==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muscatel
<hw>Mus"ca*tel`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of, pertaining to,
or designating, or derived from, a muscat grapes or similar grapes;
<as>as, <ex>muscatel</ex> grapes; <ex>muscatel</ex> wine,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muscatel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Muscatel
<hw>Mus"ca*tel`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A common name for
several varieties of rich sweet wine, made in Italy, Spain, and
France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Finest raisins, dried on the vine;
⟦ldquo⟧sun raisins.⟦rdquo⟧</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><altsp>[Variously written <asp>moscatel</asp>, <asp>muscadel</asp>,
etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muschelkalk</ent>⟦br⟧
